    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "In part, this lack of context reflects the fact that specific individual disasters are not a singular result of one or another specific policies (ie. flooding in Austin was not directly caused by legislation passed a few months ago). "
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Droughts, wildfires and floods are more nebulously worsened by an entire agenda implemented over decades, and so political context often is avoided for fear of it being labeled climate hysteria — even though that context is so critical. Worse, green policies are sometimes even blamed for the disasters. For instance, after "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            22
